fields.title: Basketball Night
fields.description: We are short of three players to complete the team for a basketball tournament
fields.requirements: Basketball shoes

fields.title: Morning Yoga Session
fields.description: Start your day with a relaxing yoga class to improve focus and flexibility.
fields.requirements: Comfortable clothing, water bottle

fields.title: AI and Machine Learning Workshop
fields.description: Learn basic AI and ML concepts in this hands-on workshop for beginners.
fields.requirements: Laptop with Python installed

fields.title: Music Festival
fields.description: Share your music in this talent contest for students.
fields.requirements: Being registered 2 weeks before

fields.title: Football Match
fields.description: Friendly football match between students. All skill levels welcome. Refreshments provided.
fields.requirements: Football cleats, team registration

fields.title: Mental Health Talk
fields.description: Learn tips on managing stress and staying positive during the semester.
fields.requirements: None

fields.title: Career Fair EAFIT 2025-2
fields.description: Meet companies offering internships and job opportunities.
fields.requirements: be in at least the sixth semester

fields.title: Real Madrid vs Barcelona Match Night
fields.description: We are going to watch the football match Real Madrid against Barcelona in Room 201, Block 33. There will be snacks and soft drinks. Come with your friends and enjoy the game.
fields.requirements: Respect the room and keep it clean

fields.title: Inter-Course Soccer Tournament
fields.description: Soccer competition between different university courses. Teams of 11 players. Registration by course.
fields.requirements: Be enrolled in an active course, bring ID, have valid medical insurance.

fields.title: EAFIT 10K Marathon
fields.description: 10-kilometer race through the university campus. Includes hydration and participation medal.
fields.requirements: Medical certificate, appropriate sports clothing, running shoes.

fields.title: Table Tennis Championship
fields.description: Individual table tennis tournament for students and employees. Single elimination format.
fields.requirements: Own racket (optional), sports clothing.

fields.title: Mixed Volleyball League
fields.description: Volleyball competition with mixed teams. 6 players per team (3 men, 3 women).
fields.requirements: Form mixed team, knee pads and sports clothing.

fields.title: Stress Management Workshop
fields.description: Practical workshop to learn academic and work stress management techniques.
fields.requirements: Notebook for taking notes, open mind.

fields.title: Ecological Walk Nutibara Hill
fields.description: Group walk to Nutibara Hill with specialized guide. Transportation included.
fields.requirements: Comfortable walking shoes, sunscreen, water.

fields.title: Aromatherapy and Relaxation Session
fields.description: Aromatherapy workshop with essential oils and deep relaxation techniques.
fields.requirements: Comfortable clothes, avoid strong perfumes.

fields.title: Aqua Aerobics
fields.description: Low-impact water exercise class. Ideal for all ages.
fields.requirements: Swimsuit, swimming cap, towel.

fields.title: Conference: Artificial Intelligence in Industry
fields.description: Master lecture on current and future applications of AI in different industrial sectors.
fields.requirements: None. Open to the entire academic community.

fields.title: Workshop: Mobile App Development
fields.description: Practical mobile application development workshop using React Native.
fields.requirements: Laptop with Node.js installed, basic JavaScript knowledge.

fields.title: Digital Entrepreneurship Seminar
fields.description: Seminar on strategies to create and scale digital startups in the Latin American context.
fields.requirements: Interest in entrepreneurship, notebook for notes.

fields.title: EAFIT Hackathon 2026
fields.description: 24-hour programming competition to solve real industry problems.
fields.requirements: Team of 2-4 programmers, laptop, programming knowledge.

fields.title: Tech Innovation Workshop
fields.description: Join us for an exciting workshop on the latest technology innovations and trends in software development.

fields.title: Basketball Tournament Finals
fields.description: Watch the final games of our annual basketball tournament. Free admission for all students.

fields.title: Art Exhibition Opening
fields.description: Experience contemporary art from local and international artists. Wine and cheese reception included.

fields.title: Networking Mixer for Entrepreneurs
fields.description: Connect with fellow entrepreneurs, investors, and business leaders. Perfect opportunity to expand your network.

fields.title: Data Science Bootcamp
fields.description: Intensive 3-day bootcamp covering Python, machine learning, and data visualization. Bring your laptop.

fields.title: Volleyball Championship
fields.description: Annual volleyball championship featuring teams from different faculties. Come support your team!
